<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath"> Venon 17th Paladin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Master</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#330000>(12/8/03 9:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> <br>
Charisma has been shown as a secondary impact on mezz through most of the studies (see the Casters Realm and Runes boards).  The impact is about 1% extra success per 10 points of charisma.<br>
<br>
I am not sure what the % impact on charm and lull are.<br>
<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Coercer of Vazelle<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whitlan>Whitlan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#330000>(12/19/03 8:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> I got 4 resists in a row while refreshing mezz today, then I looked over and realized my cha buff had faded.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It was amazing my initial mezz landed!  Luckily the group killed the primary target right about 3 seconds after mezz broke, so I only had to tank for a bit.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My cha is usually 280 (only because I haven't increased my cap yet--I could have 305 if I had my cap lifted).  This means my cha was at 255 after cha buff faded.  At 280 I seldom have a mezz resisted.  Never kept track, but off the top of my head I'd guess 1 out of at least 50 attempts.  Never ever had 4 resists in a row.  At 255 it became 4 resists in a row.  So I guess this can tell how important cha is here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gumbletinkertumble>Gumble Tinkertumble</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#330000>(12/19/03 9:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.adstainer.f2s.com/Gumble.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> I think you just got unlucky. My cha is usually a lot lower than that and I have never had 4 resists in a row. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328977" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.adstainer.f2s.com/Gumble.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328977" target="top">Sage Gumble Tinkertumble</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Coercer of 65 seasons<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Live long and Tinker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561566" target="top">Podrin 48 Beastlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660138" target="top">Fekwitt 30 Ranger</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660139" target="top">Garhedron 26 Druid</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660140" target="top">Bernard 25 Shadowknight</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660143" target="top">Jumble 27 Gnecromancer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=729936" target="top">Deuse 34 Rogue</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eidolonfaer>Eidolon Faer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#330000>(12/19/03 5:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> High Charisma becomes important if you're Pacify-pulling in a high-resist environment like BOT, or if you're Charming something that can squish you like a bug.<br>
<br>
For mezzing, it doesn't make a terribly significant difference.<br>
<br>
But Enchanter gear tends to have Charisma on it anyway.  Getting to 280 with a self-buff shouldnt require great effort, especially since nobody's likely to roll against you for CHA augs in LDoN. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whitlan>Whitlan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#330000>(12/21/03 7:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> Interesting.  Mmm, tempted to raise my cha cap now.  Pac resists squashed me a few times. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gumbletinkertumble>Gumble Tinkertumble</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#330000>(12/22/03 4:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.adstainer.f2s.com/Gumble.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> Cha doesn't help Pacify stick. It stops mobs whacking you if they do manage to resist the spell. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328977" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.adstainer.f2s.com/Gumble.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328977" target="top">Sage Gumble Tinkertumble</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Coercer of 65 seasons<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Live long and Tinker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561566" target="top">Podrin 48 Beastlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660138" target="top">Fekwitt 30 Ranger</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660139" target="top">Garhedron 26 Druid</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660140" target="top">Bernard 25 Shadowknight</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660143" target="top">Jumble 27 Gnecromancer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=729936" target="top">Deuse 34 Rogue</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whitlan>Whitlan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#330000>(12/22/03 9:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> Did someone do a test on this?  There are times when a pac was resisted the mob did not come at me, and I always thought it was cuz I was farther away from them.<br>
<br>
It seemed like every time they came at me was when I stood within a closer range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=breezantheold>Breezan the Old</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#330000>(12/22/03 11:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> According to the Devs at SOE, Charisma affects only the SECONDARY check on Pacify spells. When you try and pacify a mob, it gets 2 checks, first for the MR to see if it resists or not, if it does not resist you are flying, if it does resist a second check is made vs your charisma, this will decide if you get PWNED on an LDON hard or not, in other words will the mob agro.<br>
<br>
I have done various testing with range and Line of sight neither matter it is simple the resists. Btw, I have found that on an LDON hard with a maxed Charisma of 290 I am still getting a resist on Pacification about 1 of 3 times, usually of those resists I will get agro 50% of the time or so.<br>
<br>
One strat on staying alive in this situation is to have the MT pull agro on an add NOT the one you are targetted on. You won't have time to switch targets on the inc and are much better off just casting mez asap.<br>
<br>
Color cloud is an absolute must and has save me countless times as has the AR + ER combo.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp on this issue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whitlan>Whitlan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#330000>(12/22/03 8:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charisma~</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info and advice.  I haven't attempted a hard LDoN yet.  Whoa that's pretty tough and scary to have one resist outta 3.<br>
<br>
It's a great idea to have the MT target a possible add ahead of time.  But most of the time I'm pac'ing ahead in LDoN while the MT is still on the current fighting mob.  So does this mean in a hard adventure you pretty much can not pac ahead?  If so, it seems to call for a new strategy to save time.  What do you do to save time?<br>
<br>
